{
  "texts": [
    "First, descriptive statistics (i.e., number and percentage of studies) were computed to characterise the included user studies with regard to seven categories: meta information (e.g., year and type of publication, type of user study), technological factors (e.g., DNN model, XAI method), participants (e.g., domain expertise, AI expertise), images (e.g., general datasets like ImageNet, domain-specific images), human tasks (e.g., task focus, task assignment, cognitive requirements), experimental designs (e.g., between or within participants) and data analysis (e.g., dependent variables, reporting of statistical results).",
    "Second, an overview of the empirical outcomes was provided.",
    "It was analysed how many studies reported benefits, null effects or even costs of saliency maps and what specific biases were observed.",
    "The main analysis examined how the effects of saliency maps depended on factors related to the human tasks, AI, XAI, images, human participants and comparisons.",
    "These factors were derived from the included studies and their outcomes, instead of being predefined in advance."
  ]
}